00:31.105 --> 00:34.741
<i>♪ When you were only starting
to go to kindergarten ♪</i>

00:34.742 --> 00:38.511
<i>♪ I bet you drove the
little boys wild ♪</i>

00:38.512 --> 00:42.282
<i>♪ And when it came to
winning blue ribbons ♪</i>

00:42.283 --> 00:45.451
<i>♪ You must have shown
the other kids how ♪</i>

00:45.452 --> 00:48.054
<i>♪ I can see the judges' eyes
as they handed you the prize ♪</i>

00:48.055 --> 00:49.689
[dog collar jingles]

00:49.690 --> 00:50.790
<i>♪ I bet you made the cutest bow ♪</i>

00:50.791 --> 00:52.592
Good morning, Juno.

00:52.593 --> 00:54.861
I smell breakfast cooking. Do you?

00:54.862 --> 00:56.696
Come on.

00:56.697 --> 00:58.231
<i>♪ 'Cause, baby, look at you now ♪</i>

00:58.232 --> 01:00.265
Oh, Mother.

01:15.816 --> 01:19.419
<i>♪ Does your mother realize ♪</i>

01:19.420 --> 01:23.222
<i>♪ The stork delivered
quite a prize ♪</i>

01:23.223 --> 01:27.726
<i>♪ The day he left you
on the family tree ♪</i>

01:30.631 --> 01:34.467
<i>♪ Does your dad appreciate ♪</i>

01:34.468 --> 01:38.037
<i>♪ That you're merely super great ♪</i>

01:38.038 --> 01:42.841
<i>♪ The miracle of any century ♪</i>

01:45.346 --> 01:47.313
<i>♪ If they don't just
send them both... ♪</i>

01:47.314 --> 01:50.382
Good morning, honey. Come on and eat.

01:54.976 --> 01:58.579
Oh, so I finished putting
up those new shower curtains

01:58.580 --> 01:59.813
in the motel bathrooms.

01:59.814 --> 02:01.448
They look great.

02:01.449 --> 02:03.817
I mean, the rooms are
looking all spiffed up now.

02:03.818 --> 02:05.152
Great.

02:05.153 --> 02:06.920
Good to keep up business.

02:06.921 --> 02:09.823
Yes, and I was thinking
maybe it's time we paint.

02:09.824 --> 02:13.427
We haven't redone the exterior
of the motel in a few years now,

02:13.428 --> 02:15.297
and that hardware store just reopened.

02:16.364 --> 02:18.831
I wish I could go down to the
village with you and look.

02:20.935 --> 02:22.101
I know, Mother.

02:24.205 --> 02:25.672
I know it's hard for you always having

02:25.673 --> 02:27.374
to stay here in the house.

02:27.375 --> 02:28.942
But it's what we signed on for.

02:28.943 --> 02:31.611
And at least it's paradise here, right?

02:35.850 --> 02:38.150
Eat your biscuits, honey,
before they get cold.

02:47.695 --> 02:49.196
All righty, then, Mother.

02:49.197 --> 02:50.697
I'll see you in a bit.

02:50.698 --> 02:52.633
I imagine you will.

02:52.634 --> 02:54.066
It's not like I'm going anywhere.

02:55.470 --> 02:58.405
Sorry about the village.

02:58.406 --> 03:00.908
But it's just the same
old village, though.

03:00.909 --> 03:02.175
I know.

03:02.176 --> 03:03.911
And I'd give up a million villages

03:03.912 --> 03:05.544
just to be with you here forever.

03:11.586 --> 03:14.755
- I love you, Mother.
- I love you, Norman.

03:14.756 --> 03:16.657
<i>[Artie Shaw & Billie Holiday's
"Any Old Time" plays]</i>

03:16.658 --> 03:20.827
<i>♪ So just remember that
I am waiting, dear ♪</i>

03:20.828 --> 03:24.064
<i>♪ If ever you want
me, I'll be near ♪</i>

03:24.065 --> 03:26.966
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

03:44.085 --> 03:47.086
<i>[crackling electricity]</i>

03:50.477 --> 03:54.323
