- www.addic7ed.com -

03:56.397 --> 03:59.298
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

04:01.102 --> 04:03.502
[doors buzzing]

04:13.214 --> 04:15.214
In line, inmates!

04:20.954 --> 04:22.922
[indistinct shouting]

04:30.064 --> 04:32.932
[grunting]

04:45.146 --> 04:48.047
<i>[Frank Fafara's "Only
In My Dreams" plays]</i>

04:50.284 --> 04:52.319
<i>♪ Only in my dreams ♪</i>

04:52.320 --> 04:54.521
<i>♪ Only in my dreams ♪</i>

04:54.522 --> 04:56.923
<i>♪ Are you really mine, dear ♪</i>

04:56.924 --> 04:58.592
<i>♪ Are you really mine ♪</i>

04:58.593 --> 04:59.826
<i>♪ Only in my dreams ♪</i>

04:59.827 --> 05:01.294
[gasps] Oh, hello, Norman.

05:01.295 --> 05:02.863
Mrs. Claremont. Aww.

05:02.864 --> 05:04.331
Beautiful weather we're having, huh?

05:04.332 --> 05:06.833
- It is.
<i>- ♪ Only in my dreams ♪</i>

05:06.834 --> 05:08.935
<i>♪ Only in my dreams ♪</i>

05:08.936 --> 05:11.138
<i>♪ Do I have your love, dear ♪</i>

05:11.139 --> 05:13.473
<i>♪ Have your love ♪</i>

05:13.474 --> 05:15.108
<i>♪ Only in my dreams ♪</i>

05:15.109 --> 05:17.144
<i>♪ In the still of the night ♪</i>

05:17.145 --> 05:19.646
<i>♪ Hold you tight ♪</i>

05:19.647 --> 05:21.247
<i>♪ You say good night ♪</i>

05:23.017 --> 05:24.785
<i>♪ It's easy, baby ♪</i>

05:24.786 --> 05:28.754
<i>♪ To love you in my
dreams every night ♪</i>

05:30.725 --> 05:33.994
<i>♪ But when that sun
shines in my window ♪</i>

05:33.995 --> 05:37.330
<i>♪ You leave with the night ♪</i>

05:37.331 --> 05:39.566
<i>♪ Fade from sight ♪</i>

05:39.567 --> 05:41.867
<i>♪ Into the night ♪</i>

05:43.571 --> 05:45.405
<i>♪ Only in my dreams ♪</i>

05:45.406 --> 05:47.821
Oh, hi. Can I help you?

05:47.822 --> 05:49.810
<i>♪ Do I hold you tight, dear ♪</i>

05:49.811 --> 05:52.012
Yes, I think maybe you can.

05:52.013 --> 05:53.513
<i>♪ Only in my dreams ♪</i>

05:53.514 --> 05:56.850
This is a nice, soft, vintage yellow.

05:56.851 --> 05:58.752
Oh, yes, uh...

05:58.753 --> 06:01.188
No, that i... that is nice.

06:01.189 --> 06:02.556
This is for an exterior, right?

06:02.557 --> 06:04.157
It is.

06:04.158 --> 06:06.393
I, uh... I own and... And
manage the Bates Motel.

06:06.394 --> 06:08.762
It's... it's on the old
highway before the bypass.

06:08.763 --> 06:10.330
I've driven by there.

06:10.331 --> 06:12.032
I love your house; it's amazing.

06:12.033 --> 06:15.368
Like, what mind thought that house up?

06:15.369 --> 06:18.905
It reminds me of that Hopper painting.

06:18.906 --> 06:20.740
Oh, exactly, yes.

06:20.741 --> 06:23.743
My, uh... well, my mother and
I bought it several years back,

06:23.744 --> 06:26.413
and she was always trying to fix it up.

06:26.414 --> 06:27.948
She... she passed away,

06:27.949 --> 06:30.283
but she would've really
loved this store.

06:30.284 --> 06:31.718
<i>[jazzy big band music]</i>

06:31.719 --> 06:33.386
She was, uh...

06:33.387 --> 06:35.589
She was really very artistic

06:35.590 --> 06:39.359
and always wanted
everything to be beautiful.

06:39.360 --> 06:40.794
I think it was her way of fighting

06:40.795 --> 06:42.262
what wasn't beautiful in the world

06:42.263 --> 06:44.530
and things she just couldn't control.

06:46.234 --> 06:48.601
I totally understand that.

06:53.274 --> 06:56.209
Uh, I think I'll take these.

06:56.210 --> 06:57.776
Great.

06:59.113 --> 07:00.246
They're so good.

07:07.155 --> 07:09.956
So, uh, does your husband like paint?

07:09.957 --> 07:11.758
[laughs]

07:11.759 --> 07:13.293
Not so much, no.

07:13.294 --> 07:15.728
The store is definitely my baby.

07:17.498 --> 07:18.665
What's your name?

07:18.666 --> 07:20.333
Uh, Norman Bates.

07:20.334 --> 07:23.570
I'm Madeleine Loomis.

07:23.571 --> 07:26.273
Well, it's sure been nice meeting you.

07:26.274 --> 07:27.673
Yeah.

07:30.178 --> 07:32.812
[laughs] Now I have to
take money from you.

07:32.813 --> 07:36.215
- Ah, yes.
- So your total is $38.64.

07:45.760 --> 07:48.995
Um, I'm... I'm sorry, this isn't, uh...

07:48.996 --> 07:50.263
It's not my wallet.

07:50.264 --> 07:51.631
I... I found it in...

07:51.632 --> 07:53.033
In one of the motel rooms.

07:53.034 --> 07:54.668
I just meant to put it
in the lost and found box

07:54.669 --> 07:55.802
that I have in my office.

07:55.803 --> 07:59.005
I, um... I can't pay with this.

07:59.006 --> 08:01.508
Would... would you just hold these
items for me till I get back?

08:01.509 --> 08:02.976
- Of course.
- All righty.

08:02.977 --> 08:04.543
- Thanks. I'll be back.
- I'll be here.

08:07.682 --> 08:10.683
[indistinct chatter]

08:16.057 --> 08:19.059
<i>[foreboding music]</i>

08:19.060 --> 08:21.294
<i>[line trilling]</i>

08:21.295 --> 08:25.031
<i>Your call cannot be
accepted at this time.</i>

08:25.032 --> 08:27.132
<i>Please try your call again later</i>

08:31.572 --> 08:34.573
[vacuum whirring]

08:37.345 --> 08:38.745
Hi, honey, you're home.

08:38.746 --> 08:40.847
Have you seen my wallet anywhere?

08:40.847 --> 08:42.148
Yeah, I just saw it in your room.

08:42.149 --> 08:43.582
You must've left without it.

08:43.583 --> 08:45.218
Well, I have someone else's wallet,

08:45.219 --> 08:47.254
and I don't know how I got it.

08:47.255 --> 08:48.521
Let me see.

08:48.522 --> 08:51.390
<i>[tense music]</i>

08:55.730 --> 08:58.031
Mm, yeah.

08:58.032 --> 09:00.033
It's not your wallet.

09:00.034 --> 09:02.235
Should I put it in the mailbox?

09:02.236 --> 09:03.570
No, I wouldn't do that.

09:03.571 --> 09:05.438
No, it might belong to
someone in the motel.

09:05.439 --> 09:07.107
They'll... They'll come looking for it.

09:07.108 --> 09:09.376
I just don't remember
checking this person in.

09:09.377 --> 09:11.578
Huh.

09:11.579 --> 09:14.948
[vacuum whirring]

09:14.949 --> 09:16.415
Mother?

09:20.388 --> 09:22.422
Do you ever have the feeling that you've

09:22.423 --> 09:24.591
had the same nightmare
over and over again

09:24.592 --> 09:26.626
but that you can't remember it?

09:26.627 --> 09:29.695
You just remember the feeling of it.

09:31.532 --> 09:32.931
Nope.

09:35.603 --> 09:37.370
Just keep it in the
office. Put it in the safe.

09:37.371 --> 09:38.772
Why would I put it in the safe?

09:38.773 --> 09:40.607
Because someone might
come looking for it,

09:40.608 --> 09:41.975
and I don't want it to get lost.

09:41.976 --> 09:43.475
You know what your memory's like.

09:44.812 --> 09:46.579
I can't help it.

09:46.580 --> 09:49.616
I know, sweetheart. I know.

09:49.617 --> 09:51.418
Just do what I'm telling you, okay?

09:51.419 --> 09:53.118
Put it in the safe.

10:10.402 --> 10:12.102
Congrats on the promotion.

10:12.103 --> 10:14.238
I heard you got the
Pine Coast Ale account.

10:14.239 --> 10:16.006
Yeah, thanks.

10:16.007 --> 10:18.942
I think I, uh... I think I
finally found my calling.

10:18.943 --> 10:20.244
- Beer. Who knew?
- [chuckles]

10:20.245 --> 10:21.578
That beer would be your calling?

10:21.579 --> 10:22.980
I knew that.

10:22.981 --> 10:24.782
I'm gonna run these inside real quick.

10:24.783 --> 10:26.182
Yeah.

10:29.654 --> 10:32.122
Hey, birthday girl.

10:32.123 --> 10:34.258
Hey.

10:34.259 --> 10:35.826
How's my girls?

10:35.827 --> 10:36.927
We're good.

10:36.928 --> 10:40.097
She was a little fussy before,
but she's calmed down now.

10:40.098 --> 10:42.166
Oh.

10:42.167 --> 10:44.435
How'd I get so lucky?

10:44.436 --> 10:47.503
You had quite a tour of duty
in the lower levels of hell.

10:49.340 --> 10:51.141
Here, give her to me.

10:51.142 --> 10:52.275
Go enjoy your party.

10:53.645 --> 10:55.144
I got you. I got you.

11:00.018 --> 11:02.552
[doorbell rings] I'll get it.

11:04.856 --> 11:06.556
[doorbell rings]

11:10.295 --> 11:11.461
Hey.

11:13.031 --> 11:14.398
Oh, my gosh.

11:14.399 --> 11:15.966
Um, come in.

11:15.967 --> 11:17.634
- Appreciate it.
- Yeah.

11:17.635 --> 11:19.169
Thanks.

11:19.170 --> 11:20.637
We're just throwing a party right now.

11:20.638 --> 11:22.039
I'm sorry. Is this a bad time?

11:22.040 --> 11:23.807
I could come back if you want.

11:23.808 --> 11:25.675
Hey, Em, I think I'm gonna
cut the cake pretty soon.

11:29.914 --> 11:33.282
Caleb's here.

11:36.454 --> 11:37.720
Hey.

11:41.192 --> 11:43.025
Yeah, she's ours.

11:51.836 --> 11:53.002
Can I hold her?

11:57.175 --> 11:58.574
Yeah.

12:02.847 --> 12:05.182
Hello, Kate.

12:05.183 --> 12:06.315
[whispering] Hey.

12:08.286 --> 12:11.121
I was looking at pictures
on Emma's Facebook.

12:11.122 --> 12:13.791
Not to sound creepy, but
it was a way to make sure

12:13.792 --> 12:15.626
that you're both okay.

12:15.627 --> 12:18.695
I saw the baby.

12:18.696 --> 12:20.096
And I had to come.

12:22.100 --> 12:25.201
Man, Norma Louise must be
over the moon about this.

12:30.809 --> 12:32.876
What?

12:32.877 --> 12:35.978
I don't really talk to
my mom or Norman anymore.

12:38.550 --> 12:40.951
Wh... what happened?

12:40.952 --> 12:42.685
Look, I don't... I don't
want to talk about it.

12:47.392 --> 12:50.026
But there's a grandkid involved now.

12:51.496 --> 12:53.630
Where're you staying, Caleb?

12:53.631 --> 12:57.267
Ah, I... I haven't
checked in anywhere yet.

12:57.268 --> 12:59.603
The truth is, I'm running
a little low on funds.

12:59.604 --> 13:02.973
It took a lot of effort
to get over the border.

13:02.974 --> 13:06.743
Um, hoping maybe I could
stay here for a few nights

13:06.744 --> 13:08.177
until I figure out what I was doing.

13:09.848 --> 13:11.148
Of course you can.

13:11.149 --> 13:12.683
Yeah, we... we don't have a spare room,

13:12.684 --> 13:14.651
but I hope the couch is okay.

13:14.652 --> 13:16.385
No, that's great. Thank you, Emma.

13:19.157 --> 13:20.490
Oh, man.

13:20.491 --> 13:22.092
You want me to put my stuff somewhere?

13:22.093 --> 13:23.660
Oh, yeah, you can just dump
your stuff in our room.

13:23.661 --> 13:24.994
It's down the hall.

13:32.136 --> 13:33.470
I'm sorry.

13:33.471 --> 13:34.904
- It's okay.
- It's fine.

13:39.510 --> 13:42.411
<i>[eerie music]</i>

14:49.914 --> 14:52.815
<i>[eerie music swells]</i>

15:00.959 --> 15:03.960
[Alex grunting]

15:11.402 --> 15:12.635
Alex?

15:15.239 --> 15:17.607
I was sorry to hear
your parole got denied.

15:17.608 --> 15:19.476
[panting]

15:19.477 --> 15:22.946
I wrote nothing but positive
things in my part of the report.

15:22.947 --> 15:25.782
You work hard in your sessions.

15:25.783 --> 15:27.317
You've been a model prisoner.

15:27.318 --> 15:29.319
It's bullshit. It's politics.

15:29.320 --> 15:32.089
I'm... I'm a crooked cop,
Phil; that's what they do.

15:32.090 --> 15:33.890
Yeah, make an example out of you.

15:33.891 --> 15:35.592
Two more years. That's all I care about.

15:35.593 --> 15:39.162
[panting]

15:39.163 --> 15:41.231
<i>[dark music]</i>

15:41.232 --> 15:43.399
I know it was bad news.

15:49.807 --> 15:51.341
Yes, uh, finally.

15:51.342 --> 15:53.810
I, uh... I have a
charge from your company

15:53.811 --> 15:55.512
on my credit card bill, but

15:55.513 --> 15:57.814
I didn't order anything
from whoever you are...

15:57.815 --> 16:00.917
Northwest Science Supply.

16:00.918 --> 16:02.619
Uh, yeah, Norman Bates.

16:02.620 --> 16:04.654
Uh, October 16th.

16:04.655 --> 16:07.524
Could you tell me what
the charge is for?

16:07.525 --> 16:08.792
Luminol?

16:08.793 --> 16:10.360
Luminol, yes.

16:10.361 --> 16:12.696
No, w-well, I-I... I
don't know what that is.

16:12.697 --> 16:14.664
I have no idea. I
didn't order that, okay?

16:14.665 --> 16:15.932
So... no, no, no. No.

16:15.933 --> 16:17.167
I'm gonna get them to call you,

16:17.168 --> 16:19.902
and then we can figure this
out, because it's ridiculous.

16:28.446 --> 16:30.113
[door opens]

16:30.114 --> 16:31.782
Hi.

16:31.783 --> 16:34.851
I need a room for a few hours.

16:34.852 --> 16:37.120
Oh, uh, a few hours?

16:37.121 --> 16:39.556
That's right. What is
it, uh, 50, 60 bucks?

16:39.557 --> 16:42.492
No, we don't rent rooms for a few hours.

16:42.493 --> 16:43.960
This is the Bates Motel.

16:43.961 --> 16:45.729
We're not that kind of establishment.

16:45.730 --> 16:47.864
[chuckles]

16:47.865 --> 16:49.166
Okay.

16:49.167 --> 16:51.634
Uh, how much for a night?

16:52.670 --> 16:54.204
$120.

16:54.205 --> 16:55.638
Including tax.

16:58.576 --> 17:00.309
There you go.

17:02.146 --> 17:03.914
Can I have a key?

17:03.915 --> 17:06.083
Uh...

17:06.084 --> 17:07.316
Your name?

17:10.021 --> 17:12.122
David.

17:12.123 --> 17:14.824
David Davidson.

17:20.431 --> 17:21.698
Uh, that's my name.

17:21.699 --> 17:23.467
You don't need any other information.

17:23.468 --> 17:25.935
There's the money. May I have a key?

17:39.917 --> 17:42.085
Do let me know if I can
do anything else for you,

17:42.086 --> 17:43.953
Mr. David Davidson.

17:46.724 --> 17:49.592
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

19:00.264 --> 19:02.999
I can't stand not seeing you.

19:03.000 --> 19:04.367
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

19:04.368 --> 19:05.768
I want you so bad.

19:31.262 --> 19:34.263
[woman moans, phone rings]

19:36.334 --> 19:38.568
Bates Motel. Norman speaking.

19:38.569 --> 19:41.770
<i>Norman, what are you doing?</i>

19:42.840 --> 19:44.708
Nothing.

19:44.709 --> 19:48.411
<i>Okay, well, close up the
office and come upstairs.</i>

19:48.412 --> 19:50.046
<i>Dinner's gonna get cold.</i>

19:50.047 --> 19:51.681
Okay, Mother.

19:51.682 --> 19:53.716
I'm just coming. I'll...
I'll be right there.

20:00.024 --> 20:02.891
[breathing deeply]

20:14.593 --> 20:17.127
Norman? Is that you?

20:22.668 --> 20:24.169
There you are.

20:24.170 --> 20:27.005
Did you buy something called luminol?

20:27.006 --> 20:28.907
No, not that I remember.

20:28.908 --> 20:30.775
Are you sure you didn't order it?

20:30.776 --> 20:34.012
No, I didn't order anything.

20:34.013 --> 20:36.114
Do you know what it is?

20:36.115 --> 20:39.584
Uh, no... it just sounds
like a cleaning product.

20:39.585 --> 20:41.319
Come and sit down.

20:41.320 --> 20:43.154
I'm sure the receipt's
somewhere in the house.

20:43.155 --> 20:44.388
Come.

20:51.697 --> 20:54.499
I hate having blackouts.

20:54.500 --> 20:58.403
Well, you could start
taking your medicine again.

20:58.404 --> 20:59.937
I don't want to take it, Mother.

21:07.112 --> 21:09.314
I saw the paint swatches.

21:09.315 --> 21:11.149
I like the yellow for the motel.

21:11.150 --> 21:12.951
It's exactly the color
I would've picked out.

21:12.952 --> 21:14.185
Oh, good.

21:14.186 --> 21:15.520
It was the woman who runs the store

21:15.521 --> 21:17.455
who actually picked it out.

21:17.456 --> 21:19.524
Who is she?

21:19.525 --> 21:22.393
Oh... oh, she's just a woman.

21:22.394 --> 21:25.797
Uh, Madeleine. I think that's her name.

21:25.798 --> 21:27.131
Yeah, Madeleine Loomis.

21:27.132 --> 21:29.300
Loomis? That's a funny name.

21:29.301 --> 21:30.835
A name's a name.

21:30.836 --> 21:34.072
And, uh, she's very nice.

21:34.073 --> 21:36.307
She's... she's very artistic.

21:36.308 --> 21:37.575
You know, it's a big job

21:37.576 --> 21:39.377
painting this place all by myself,

21:39.378 --> 21:41.312
and I just think she'll be helpful.

21:41.313 --> 21:43.715
<i>[eerie music]</i>

21:43.716 --> 21:47.051
How old is she?

21:47.052 --> 21:48.987
She's...

21:48.988 --> 21:50.619
- [stammering]
- What?

21:50.620 --> 21:51.723
I don't know.

21:51.724 --> 21:53.224
[stammering] Y-y-you know
I'm... you know I'm...

21:53.225 --> 21:54.259
You know I'm just bad at guessing ages.

21:54.260 --> 21:55.727
40, 50, 60?

21:55.728 --> 21:57.428
I'd say late 20s.

21:57.429 --> 21:59.230
Ah.

21:59.231 --> 22:02.133
And what does that mean, "ah"?

22:02.134 --> 22:04.035
Ah, it means "ah,"

22:04.036 --> 22:07.272
as in, "Oh, how about that?"

22:07.273 --> 22:09.774
First of all, Mother, she is married.

22:09.775 --> 22:10.875
Oh, that can be irrelevant.

22:10.876 --> 22:13.211
No, second of all,

22:13.212 --> 22:15.246
she works in a store,

22:15.247 --> 22:18.116
and I'm going to go in and
just buy some paint from her.

22:18.117 --> 22:19.951
So do you really have
a problem with that?

22:19.952 --> 22:21.118
- No.
- Good.

22:23.956 --> 22:25.356
I just don't know what you're thinking.

22:25.357 --> 22:26.924
Mother, I'm not thinking anything.

22:26.925 --> 22:29.527
She is just a nice girl.

22:29.528 --> 22:32.096
Would it really be that
awful if I had a friend?

22:32.097 --> 22:33.464
Oh, here we go.

22:33.465 --> 22:35.266
Oh, Mother, what is wrong with you?

22:35.267 --> 22:36.734
What is wrong with me?

22:36.735 --> 22:38.703
Well, let me see, for, uh...

22:38.704 --> 22:40.571
Let's see, for starters,

22:40.572 --> 22:42.373
I am dead.

22:42.374 --> 22:43.941
And why am I pretending to be dead?

22:43.942 --> 22:46.244
So I could get away from everyone

22:46.245 --> 22:49.547
and everything that could
distract me from you, okay?

22:49.548 --> 22:50.948
I know that, and I appreciate it.

22:50.949 --> 22:52.917
You appreciate it?

22:52.918 --> 22:55.219
Appreciate, like I baked you
a coffee cake or something?

22:55.220 --> 22:57.955
I spend 24/7 in this house

22:57.956 --> 22:59.557
looking after you, feeding you,

22:59.558 --> 23:01.292
bolstering your moods,
doing your laundry.

23:01.293 --> 23:02.894
I can't leave!

23:02.895 --> 23:04.962
I can't go anywhere!
I'm going nuts here!

23:04.963 --> 23:08.566
I literally gave up my
life to protect you.

23:08.567 --> 23:11.235
Okay? To give you a
life without trouble.

23:11.236 --> 23:13.137
And we're doing it,
right? We're doing it.

23:13.138 --> 23:16.107
I mean, a mentally ill
boy and a dead woman.

23:16.108 --> 23:18.276
We're actually doing it.
We're... we have customers.

23:18.277 --> 23:20.144
We... we... we have a life.

23:20.145 --> 23:21.412
I know, and I appreciate it.

23:21.413 --> 23:23.414
Stop saying you appreciate it!

23:23.415 --> 23:26.283
<i>[tense music]</i>

23:39.832 --> 23:41.231
I'm sorry, Mother.

23:43.969 --> 23:45.569
It's not fair to you. I know that.

23:50.509 --> 23:53.111
It's not that, okay? It's
not... it's not that.

23:53.112 --> 23:55.546
It's that...

23:55.547 --> 23:58.616
you... you just can't have
other people in your life.

23:58.617 --> 24:02.620
I mean, what are you
gonna do? Bring her over?

24:02.621 --> 24:04.355
I mean, where am I
gonna go? In a closet?

24:04.356 --> 24:05.990
I'm not gonna bring her here to dinner.

24:05.991 --> 24:08.626
[stammering] It's...
this... This is absurd.

24:08.627 --> 24:11.362
I know you, Norman.

24:11.363 --> 24:14.532
Come on, I know you. I know
you better than anyone.

24:14.533 --> 24:16.167
You can't have other
people in your life,

24:16.168 --> 24:17.502
especially women.

24:17.503 --> 24:20.505
You're just making my job harder.

24:20.506 --> 24:22.407
Your job?

24:22.408 --> 24:24.775
Protecting you.

24:26.345 --> 24:27.778
Do you understand?

24:40.692 --> 24:42.160
I'm not hungry.

24:42.161 --> 24:43.694
Mother...

24:43.695 --> 24:44.828
[door slams open]

25:46.959 --> 25:49.860
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

26:10.415 --> 26:13.417
[motor humming]

26:13.418 --> 26:16.286
<i>[dark music]</i>

26:36.041 --> 26:39.176
What dream am I in, Mother?

26:39.177 --> 26:42.078
<i>[dramatic music swells]</i>

26:48.629 --> 26:51.031
[whispering] Hi. Hi.

26:51.032 --> 26:52.566
Good morning.

26:52.567 --> 26:54.034
You get some sleep?

26:54.035 --> 26:56.837
Yeah, I did. It was amazing.

26:56.838 --> 26:58.071
[grunts]

26:58.072 --> 26:59.305
Hello.

27:01.576 --> 27:03.009
Where's Caleb?

27:03.010 --> 27:05.512
Uh, he went to town to get some...

27:05.513 --> 27:07.914
Some bagels and coffee.

27:07.915 --> 27:09.148
Oh, that's sweet.

27:12.153 --> 27:15.722
You know, um, uh...

27:15.723 --> 27:18.024
[stammering] I'm k... I'm kind
of starting to get the feeling

27:18.025 --> 27:20.560
that he wants to move here to Seattle

27:20.561 --> 27:22.596
to be near us.

27:22.597 --> 27:24.230
Yeah, I have that feeling, too.

27:30.171 --> 27:32.338
[stammering] I don't... I
don't know what to say to him.

27:34.709 --> 27:37.411
I mean...

27:37.412 --> 27:39.112
I don't know... he's... He's my dad,

27:39.113 --> 27:42.281
and he's... he's trying
to make an effort.

27:43.384 --> 27:44.617
[whispering] Yeah.

27:47.088 --> 27:48.854
The truth is, Em...

27:51.926 --> 27:54.027
Caleb came up with a bunch of money

27:54.028 --> 27:55.628
to help pay for your transplant.

27:57.031 --> 27:58.799
He did?

27:58.800 --> 28:00.066
Yeah.

28:00.067 --> 28:02.068
<i>[somber music]</i>

28:02.069 --> 28:03.737
Yeah, and it... it was really dangerous,

28:03.738 --> 28:05.071
but he... but he did it to help me,

28:05.072 --> 28:06.872
because he knew how much I loved you.

28:08.409 --> 28:09.810
Dylan.

28:09.811 --> 28:11.645
He didn't want me to tell you, and I...

28:11.646 --> 28:12.978
I never wanted to tell you.

28:15.082 --> 28:16.817
It's... but...

28:16.818 --> 28:19.052
You know, I feel like we're
the only family that he has,

28:19.053 --> 28:21.588
and, I mean, he... He
can't go live by Norma.

28:21.589 --> 28:25.425
H... how can I turn him away?

28:25.426 --> 28:27.627
I... I don't know, I feel like I...

28:27.628 --> 28:29.128
Like I have to give him a chance.

28:33.835 --> 28:35.634
[sighs] [whispering] I don't know.

28:37.405 --> 28:38.938
I don't know, Kate.

28:52.653 --> 28:55.554
<i>[eerie music]</i>

29:05.933 --> 29:08.101
- Mother.
- [door opens]

29:08.102 --> 29:09.569
Hello?

29:09.570 --> 29:10.836
[bell dings]

29:17.445 --> 29:18.945
<i>[warm music]</i>

29:18.946 --> 29:20.379
Hi.

29:22.517 --> 29:24.718
I brought you some sample cans of paint

29:24.719 --> 29:27.721
and brushes so you can
try out the colors.

29:27.722 --> 29:29.455
Well, that's incredibly kind of you.

29:32.693 --> 29:34.027
Oh, I found my wallet, actually.

29:34.028 --> 29:35.662
You can pay me later.

29:35.663 --> 29:36.997
I felt bad; I should've just
told you that yesterday.

29:36.998 --> 29:38.231
No, no... Oh, no, no, no.

29:38.232 --> 29:40.366
I was actually gonna
stop by later today.

29:43.070 --> 29:44.270
Thank you.

29:48.976 --> 29:50.477
Let me walk you to your car.

29:50.478 --> 29:52.278
Okay, good.

30:00.821 --> 30:04.124
This place is awfully cute.

30:04.125 --> 30:06.326
We, uh... I... I like it.

30:06.327 --> 30:08.361
I'd love to see the house.

30:08.362 --> 30:10.530
Oh, yeah, well, I'd
love to show it to you.

30:10.531 --> 30:12.399
It's just a little bit
of a mess right now, so.

30:12.400 --> 30:15.068
You live here all alone
since your mom died?

30:15.069 --> 30:17.037
Uh-huh.

30:17.038 --> 30:19.939
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

30:22.777 --> 30:25.911
I mean, there's the guests,
of course, so that helps.

30:30.051 --> 30:34.421
You know, there's a lot of
things you can get involved in.

30:34.422 --> 30:38.425
There's a small business
owners' meeting tonight in town.

30:38.426 --> 30:41.361
You have a small
business. You should come.

30:41.362 --> 30:45.365
It's tonight at 7:00
in the old courthouse.

30:45.366 --> 30:48.268
I... I would really like to.

30:48.269 --> 30:50.302
I'm just not sure that I could get away.

30:51.606 --> 30:53.940
Well, think about it...

30:53.941 --> 30:56.276
If you can come to the meeting.

30:56.277 --> 30:57.710
Yes, I will.

31:26.907 --> 31:28.007
[dishes clatter]

31:32.513 --> 31:33.847
[chuckles]

31:33.848 --> 31:35.281
Oh, God. I hope I didn't wake you up.

31:35.282 --> 31:37.851
[laughs] I'm sorry.
I was just so hungry.

31:37.852 --> 31:40.153
You ever wake up in the
middle of the night,

31:40.154 --> 31:41.821
and you just need to eat something?

31:41.822 --> 31:43.123
Oh, my God, all the time,

31:43.124 --> 31:46.159
especially in my second trimester.

31:46.160 --> 31:48.928
I ate so much.

31:48.929 --> 31:50.929
[both laughing]

31:53.334 --> 31:57.303
Were you, um, scared?

31:57.304 --> 31:59.205
I mean, being pregnant?

31:59.206 --> 32:00.940
Oh, yeah.

32:00.941 --> 32:02.175
Yeah, I mean, it happened.

32:02.176 --> 32:04.544
We did not plan it, but...

32:04.545 --> 32:08.415
I just felt so strong,

32:08.416 --> 32:11.016
like life had given me a second chance.

32:13.688 --> 32:15.722
Can I... can I talk to
you about something?

32:15.723 --> 32:18.124
Yeah, of course.

32:18.125 --> 32:20.860
Well, I want to thank you.

32:20.861 --> 32:22.529
For...

32:22.530 --> 32:24.531
what?

32:24.532 --> 32:26.700
For what you did for me

32:26.701 --> 32:28.334
to help me get the surgery.

32:28.335 --> 32:30.537
<i>[dramatic music]</i>

32:30.538 --> 32:31.871
I can't tell you.

32:31.872 --> 32:33.906
I never dreamed before
of having a real life.

32:35.376 --> 32:37.744
I knew I was gonna die.

32:37.745 --> 32:40.612
But you stopped that.

32:42.283 --> 32:46.618
And I will always, always be grateful.

32:47.755 --> 32:51.224
It was my pleasure.

32:51.225 --> 32:52.624
Truly.

32:58.899 --> 33:00.032
But you have to leave.

33:05.506 --> 33:08.407
It kills me to say this, but...

33:10.010 --> 33:11.745
You being here is gonna force Dylan

33:11.746 --> 33:13.012
to live a lie with his daughter

33:13.013 --> 33:14.446
every time you're in the house.

33:17.017 --> 33:18.451
I don't know the exact circumstances

33:18.452 --> 33:20.019
of how he came into this world,

33:20.020 --> 33:22.021
but I know enough to know

33:22.022 --> 33:23.989
that you're putting him
in an impossible position.

33:29.864 --> 33:32.265
I understand.

33:32.266 --> 33:35.334
- I wish it could be different.
- It's okay.

33:37.171 --> 33:40.105
I guess my coming here was kind of...

33:41.976 --> 33:43.942
It was my own self-denial.

33:45.613 --> 33:47.846
I know you're right.

33:55.723 --> 33:58.291
Hey, you should get back to sleep.

33:58.292 --> 34:00.460
Don't worry about anything.

34:00.461 --> 34:01.928
I'll just, um...

34:01.929 --> 34:03.797
I'll clean up here when I'm done

34:03.798 --> 34:05.364
and turn the lights out.

34:07.601 --> 34:09.302
It's all good.

34:09.303 --> 34:10.435
Thank you.

34:15.842 --> 34:16.975
[sighs]

34:38.920 --> 34:40.188
Are you going somewhere?

34:40.188 --> 34:43.291
Oh, yes, actually, there's this...

34:43.292 --> 34:45.793
boring meeting in town
for small business owners.

34:45.793 --> 34:48.428
I just thought I probably should attend.

34:51.199 --> 34:54.702
Small business owners
as in hardware stores?

34:54.703 --> 34:55.969
Mother...

34:55.971 --> 34:57.805
It's fine. Go ahead.

34:57.806 --> 34:59.473
- Really?
- Yeah, go ahead.

34:59.474 --> 35:02.109
But you can't take the car.

35:02.110 --> 35:04.644
Why not? It's not like you need it.

35:06.381 --> 35:08.282
You aren't supposed to be driving.

35:08.283 --> 35:09.884
I have driven the car, you know, Mother.

35:09.885 --> 35:11.385
Many times. You know that.

35:11.386 --> 35:13.221
But you shouldn't be;
you have blackouts.

35:13.222 --> 35:15.823
<i>[suspenseful music]</i>

35:15.824 --> 35:17.658
Is this just your passive-aggressive way

35:17.659 --> 35:19.460
of getting me not to go to the meeting?

35:19.461 --> 35:21.796
You know, Norman, sometimes
you can be so full of yourself.

35:21.797 --> 35:23.564
No, no... this is not my way

35:23.565 --> 35:25.666
of keeping you from doing anything

35:25.667 --> 35:27.802
except having blackouts
while you're driving.

35:27.803 --> 35:29.804
Okay? Just walk.

35:29.805 --> 35:31.305
You know what?

35:31.306 --> 35:33.307
I don't have time to just walk, Mother.

35:33.308 --> 35:35.643
I'll miss most of it.

35:35.644 --> 35:37.744
I think I'm gonna drive.

35:52.027 --> 35:54.561
[engine turns over]

35:59.935 --> 36:01.201
[tires screeching]

36:04.606 --> 36:06.974
Mother...

36:06.975 --> 36:08.676
get back in that house right now.

36:08.677 --> 36:10.044
You should not be out here.

36:10.045 --> 36:11.946
Well, you shouldn't be driving.

36:11.947 --> 36:14.181
If you're not gonna live by the rules,
I'm not gonna live by the rules.

36:14.182 --> 36:15.449
Keep your voice down!

36:15.450 --> 36:16.684
[whispering] You are
gonna get us caught!

36:16.685 --> 36:18.119
- Okay...
- What are you trying to prove?

36:18.120 --> 36:20.688
Norman, you do not have autonomy here.

36:20.689 --> 36:22.823
You can't just make unilateral decisions

36:22.824 --> 36:25.126
about everybody else, like
you're the little dictator.

36:25.127 --> 36:26.627
I am just driving to a meeting.

36:26.628 --> 36:28.529
Oh, I know what you're doing,

36:28.530 --> 36:30.064
and I know why you're doing it.

36:30.065 --> 36:32.033
I know everything about you...

36:32.034 --> 36:33.701
What scares you, what you want,

36:33.702 --> 36:35.136
what you Google.

36:35.137 --> 36:37.138
Oh, so you're looking
on my computer now?

36:37.139 --> 36:38.806
Yeah, that's what I'm doing,
looking at your computer.

36:38.807 --> 36:39.907
No, I'm not looking at your computer.

36:39.908 --> 36:41.342
I know you.

36:41.343 --> 36:43.377
I know you better than
you know yourself.

36:43.378 --> 36:45.079
And that's why you make me so angry...

36:45.080 --> 36:47.715
Because you keep doing shit that
just makes more work for me.

36:47.716 --> 36:50.051
Asking me questions that I
can't give you answers to

36:50.052 --> 36:52.019
because I'm just trying
to take care of you.

36:52.020 --> 36:54.855
Well, who asked you to take care of me?

36:54.856 --> 36:56.891
What do you think you're
trying to protect me from?

36:56.892 --> 36:58.893
No one is trying to hurt me.

36:58.894 --> 37:00.828
Fine!

37:00.829 --> 37:02.496
Come with me!

37:02.497 --> 37:05.365
<i>[tense string music]</i>

37:12.941 --> 37:14.608
You want to see what I do for you?

37:14.609 --> 37:16.911
No, I don't, Mother.
Let's just drop this.

37:16.912 --> 37:18.078
A little late for that.

37:19.748 --> 37:21.749
Look in here.

37:21.750 --> 37:23.050
I don't want to look in there.

37:23.051 --> 37:24.285
Mother, never mind, okay?

37:24.286 --> 37:25.753
Do you remember the night

37:25.754 --> 37:26.954
you were putting up the shower curtains?

37:26.955 --> 37:28.289
No.

37:28.290 --> 37:29.357
Do you remember a man showing up?

37:29.358 --> 37:31.358
No, Mother, no, I don't.

37:35.297 --> 37:36.830
You Norman Bates?

37:39.368 --> 37:41.569
I don't want to remember.
I don't want to remember.

37:41.570 --> 37:43.503
It's too late!

37:47.442 --> 37:49.443
Why was he trying to kill me, Mother?

37:49.444 --> 37:51.145
I don't know.

37:51.146 --> 37:52.947
How did you get into
the room so quickly?

37:52.948 --> 37:55.783
Huh? Why were you even outside?

37:55.784 --> 37:57.284
I don't know.

37:57.285 --> 37:58.786
What is wrong with us, Mother?

37:58.787 --> 38:01.288
I don't know, Norman! I don't know!

38:01.289 --> 38:02.422
[slicing]

38:09.898 --> 38:13.100
All I know is that the
world is full of bad people.

38:13.101 --> 38:15.970
And we cannot trust
anyone from the outside.

38:15.971 --> 38:18.773
It is you and me, Norman.
That is all we have.

38:18.774 --> 38:20.975
We would die without each
other, do you understand that?

38:20.976 --> 38:24.979
<i>[somber music]</i>

38:24.980 --> 38:26.746
Yes, Mother, I understand.

38:32.854 --> 38:34.454
It's gonna be okay.

38:50.505 --> 38:53.340
Well, it's not like we
haven't done this before.

38:53.341 --> 38:55.709
We've just got to get rid of him.

38:55.710 --> 38:59.547
Well, I was gonna put him in
the car while you were out...

38:59.548 --> 39:03.117
Just dump him somewhere
while you were out.

39:03.118 --> 39:05.385
That's why I needed the car.

39:07.956 --> 39:10.857
Well, let's just get started.

39:12.227 --> 39:15.229
<i>[Etta James' "At Last" plays]</i>

39:15.230 --> 39:18.131
<i>[slow jazzy music]</i>

39:31.346 --> 39:34.547
<i>♪ At last ♪</i>

39:39.921 --> 39:43.990
<i>♪ My love has come along ♪</i>

39:48.196 --> 39:51.832
<i>♪ My lonely days ♪</i>

39:51.833 --> 39:54.134
<i>♪ Are over ♪</i>

39:56.838 --> 40:00.406
<i>♪ And life is like a song ♪</i>

40:04.779 --> 40:07.681
<i>♪ Oh, yeah, yeah ♪</i>

40:07.682 --> 40:09.482
<i>♪ At last ♪</i>

40:13.555 --> 40:17.357
<i>♪ The stars above are blue ♪</i>

40:21.830 --> 40:26.933
<i>♪ My heart was
wrapped up in clover ♪</i>

40:30.739 --> 40:34.440
<i>♪ The night I looked at you ♪</i>

40:40.782 --> 40:43.349
<i>♪ I found a dream ♪</i>

40:44.920 --> 40:47.087
<i>♪ That I could speak to ♪</i>

40:47.088 --> 40:48.822
Look at the moon.

40:48.823 --> 40:52.593
It's so pretty how it
reflects on the water.

40:52.594 --> 40:55.528
You just couldn't make nature up
in a million years, could you?

40:56.998 --> 40:59.300
No, Mother, I don't suppose you could.

40:59.301 --> 41:01.135
<i>♪ I found a thrill ♪</i>

41:01.136 --> 41:04.505
<i>♪ To press my cheek to ♪</i>

41:04.506 --> 41:07.007
Mother?

41:07.008 --> 41:10.444
Yes, honey?

41:10.445 --> 41:13.480
What are we trying to do, exactly?

41:13.481 --> 41:17.151
<i>♪ Oh, yeah, yeah, you smiled ♪</i>

41:17.152 --> 41:19.353
What everyone's trying to do...

41:19.354 --> 41:21.322
Just trying to survive.

41:21.323 --> 41:25.526
<i>♪ Oh, and then the spell was cast ♪</i>

41:25.527 --> 41:28.762
But why was he trying to kill me?

41:28.763 --> 41:30.164
I don't know.

